attributes: {'super-study-id': 1, 'title': 'Tara Oceans', 'description': 'The Tara Oceans expedition (Karsenti et al. 2011) has collected seawater samples from all over the globe. This umbrella project collects together the MGnify analyses of Tara Oceans microbiome datasets and derived data, including assembled datasets, offering in-depth insight into microbial life in the world’s oceans.', 'image-url': '/metagenomics/images/tara.png', 'biomes-count': 0}

{'super-study-id': 2, 'title': 'Earth Microbiome Project', 'description': 'The Earth Microbiome Project is now available in MGnify. The Earth Microbiome Project (EMP) is a wide ranging collaborative effort that attempts to characterise the taxonomic and functional diversity of microbial life on the planet. Founded in 2010, the project includes 96 different studies, comprising approximately 26k individual sequencing runs from a diverse range of biomes.', 'image-url': '/metagenomics/images/emp.png', 'biomes-count': 0}

{'super-study-id': 3, 'title': 'NASA GeneLab Microbiome (MANGO)', 'description': 'Project MANGO provides access to the microbiomes of the international space station and a range of environments selected by NASA GeneLab and the JPL interplanetary protection team. These data have been collected in order to help us understand how microbial communities adapt to spaceflight and related terrestrial stresses.\r\nThis super study contains analysis of the MANGO data and related publicly available data sets.', 'image-url': '/metagenomics/images/nasa-mango.png', 'biomes-count': 0}

{'super-study-id': 4, 'title': 'HoloFood', 'description': 'Holistic approach to improve the efficiency of food production systems by deciphering the biomolecular and physiological processes triggered by incorporating feed additives and novel sustainable feeds in farmed animals.', 'image-url': '/metagenomics/images/holofood.png', 'biomes-count': 0}

{'super-study-id': 5, 'title': 'Malaspina', 'description': 'The Malaspina circumnavigation expedition was an interdisciplinary research project undertaken in 2010-2011 to assess the impact of global change on the oceans and explore their biodiversity. The project was under the umbrella of the Spanish Ministry of Science and Innovation’s Consolider-Ingenio 2010 programme. \r\nThis superstudy collects together the MGnify analyses of Malaspina microbiome datasets and derived data.', 'image-url': '/metagenomics/images/malaspina2010.png', 'biomes-count': 0}
